fields.value: Climate and developmental plasticity: interannual variability in grapevine leaf morphology

dsDescriptionValue.value: This is a set of leaf images collected from vines of various species in the genus Vitis from the USDA germplasm repository in Geneva, NY. The images show the abaxial side of leaves collected from a single shoot per vine. The file name indicates the vine ID and the appended letter indicates which image of the series the file represents for that vine. Next to each leaf is a label indicating the node position from which the leaf was sampled (as measured in plastochrons from the tip of the shoot). This dataset was collected the second week of June 2015, and continues a previous dataset (measured from the same vines) collected during the second week of June 2013.

datasetVersion.citation: Chitwood, Dan, 2015, "Climate and developmental plasticity: interannual variability in grapevine leaf morphology", doi:10.7910/DVN/KOG6SY, Harvard Dataverse, V1
